SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 25
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to propose an amendment to Article I, Section 15
of the Constitution of Tennessee, relative to bail.
WHEREAS, Senate Joint Resolution No. 919 of the One Hundred Thirteenth General
Assembly, which proposed amendment of Article 1, Section 15 of the Constitution of
Tennessee, relative to bail, was considered and agreed to by a majority of all the members
elected to each of the two houses, as shown by the yeas and nays entered on their journals;
and
WHEREAS, on April 23, 2024, such resolution proposing such amendment was
published in compliance with Article XI, Section 3 of the Constitution of Tennessee; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that a two-thirds majority of all the members elected to
each house concurring, as shown by the yeas and nays entered on their journals, that it is
proposed that Article I, Section 15 of the Constitution of Tennessee be amended by deleting the
following:
That all prisoners shall be bailable by sufficient sureties, unless for capital
offences, when the proof is evident, or the presumption great. And the privilege of the
writ of Habeas Corpus shall not be suspended, unless when in case of rebellion or
invasion, the General Assembly shall declare the public safety requires it.
and substituting instead the following:
(a) All prisoners shall be bailable by sufficient sureties unless for the following
when the proof is evident or the presumption great:
